---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro'

const lastUpdated = '18 May 2026'
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy"
  description="Union's privacy promise: what we collect, where it goes, what's never shared."
>
  <article class="prose-union">
    <h1 class="font-prayer text-5xl text-union-charcoal">Privacy</h1>
    <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-union-secondary">
      Last updated: {lastUpdated}
    </p>

    <p class="mt-8 text-lg leading-relaxed">
      This page explains exactly what data Union collects, where it
      lives, who else sees it, and how to delete it. If anything here is
      unclear, email
      <a class="text-union-gold underline" href="mailto:hello@unionwith.app"
      >hello@unionwith.app</a>.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-12 font-prayer text-3xl text-union-charcoal">
      The promise
    </h2>
    <p class="mt-3 text-lg leading-relaxed">
      What you share in Union is yours. We don&apos;t sell it. We
      don&apos;t share it. We don&apos;t use it to train AI models.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-12 font-prayer text-3xl text-union-charcoal">
      What we collect
    </h2>
    <ul class="mt-3 space-y-3 text-lg leading-relaxed">
      <li>
        <strong>Account details</strong> — your email address (for
        sign-in) and, if you set one, a name to greet you by.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Check-ins</strong> — the free-text descriptions you
        write to find a prayer.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Saved prayers and reflections</strong> — the prayers
        you bookmark to your journal, any reflections you write
        alongside them, and any &ldquo;answered&rdquo; notes you add.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Profile preferences</strong> — optional fields like your
        Christian tradition or season of life, used to make the
        prayers Union suggests fit you better.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p class="mt-4 text-lg leading-relaxed">
      We do not collect device identifiers, location, contacts,
      photos, advertising IDs, or analytics about how you use the app.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-12 font-prayer text-3xl text-union-charcoal">
      Where it lives
    </h2>
    <p class="mt-3 text-lg leading-relaxed">
      Everything you create in Union is stored in our Supabase
      project, hosted in the EU. Database rows are scoped to your
      account via row-level security — only you (signed in) and
      Union&apos;s own server can read them.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-12 font-prayer text-3xl text-union-charcoal">
      The AI vendors
    </h2>
    <p class="mt-3 text-lg leading-relaxed">
      When you tell Union what&apos;s on your heart, your check-in
      text is sent to two AI providers so we can find prayers that
      match it:
    </p>
    <ul class="mt-3 space-y-3 text-lg leading-relaxed">
      <li>
        <strong>OpenAI</strong> — receives your check-in text to
        compute an embedding (a numeric fingerprint used to find
        similar prayers in our corpus).
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Anthropic</strong> — receives your check-in text plus a
        short list of candidate prayers, and chooses which fit best
        plus writes a brief pastoral note.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p class="mt-4 text-lg leading-relaxed">
      We deliberately do <em>not</em> send your name, email, or any
      other identifier with these calls. The vendors see content but
      cannot link it back to your Union account.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-4 text-lg leading-relaxed">
      Both vendors, on their standard API tier, retain the request
      payload for up to 30 days for abuse-monitoring purposes and
      then delete it. Neither uses API data to train their models.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-12 font-prayer text-3xl text-union-charcoal">
      Your rights
    </h2>
    <ul class="mt-3 space-y-3 text-lg leading-relaxed">
      <li>
        <strong>See your data</strong> — everything Union holds about
        you is visible inside the app: your name in Settings, your
        check-ins on Home, your saved prayers in the Journal.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Delete your account</strong> — Settings → Delete
        account. Type <code>delete</code> to confirm. This removes
        your account row, every check-in, every saved prayer and
        reflection, and every related row across our database, in a
        single transaction.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Vendor copies</strong> — the brief retention windows at
        OpenAI and Anthropic age out on their own. We cannot force an
        instant deletion at those vendors but the windows are short
        (≤30 days) and bounded.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="mt-12 font-prayer text-3xl text-union-charcoal">
      Children
    </h2>
    <p class="mt-3 text-lg leading-relaxed">
      Union is not directed at children under 13. If you believe a
      child has signed up, email us and we&apos;ll delete the account.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-12 font-prayer text-3xl text-union-charcoal">
      Changes
    </h2>
    <p class="mt-3 text-lg leading-relaxed">
      If we change anything material on this page, we&apos;ll update
      the &ldquo;last updated&rdquo; date above and surface a notice in
      the app for at least a week.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-12 font-prayer text-3xl text-union-charcoal">
      Contact
    </h2>
    <p class="mt-3 text-lg leading-relaxed">
      Privacy questions, deletion confirmations, or anything else
      —
      <a class="text-union-gold underline" href="mailto:hello@unionwith.app"
      >hello@unionwith.app</a>.
    </p>
  </article>
</Layout>
